refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
mixedvar_export mixedexpression boolreturn
var_export gets structured information about the given variable. It is similar to var_dump with one exception: the returned representation is valid PHP code.

&reftitle.changelog;







     &Version;
     &Description;





     5.1.0

      Possibility to export classes and arrays containing classes using the
      __set_state magic
      method.

  &reftitle.examples;



    var_export Examples


<?php
$a = array (1, 2, array ("a", "b", "c"));
var_export($a);
?>


    &example.outputs;


array (
  0 => 1,
  1 => 2,
  2 => 
  array (
    0 => 'a',
    1 => 'b',
    2 => 'c',
  ),
)




<?php

$b = 3.1;
$v = var_export($b, true);
echo $v;

?>


    &example.outputs;


3.1







    Exporting classes since PHP 5.1.0


<?php
class A { public $var; }
$a = new A;
$a->var = 5;
var_export($a);
?>


    &example.outputs;


A::__set_state(array(
   'var' => 5,
))

&reftitle.notes;



  Variables of type resource couldn't be exported by this
  function.
